quran[8]{c,v,t}:
  28,6,"And to stablish them in the land; and to make Pharaoh and Haman and their hosts, the eye-witnesses of what they dreaded from them"
  28,7,"And we said by revelation to the mother of Moses, \"Give him suck; and if thou fearest for him, launch him on the sea; and fear not, neither fret; for we will restore him to thee, and make him one of the apostles"
  28,8,"And Pharaoh's family took him up to be a foe and a sorrow to them, for sinners were Pharaoh and Haman and their hosts"
  28,9,"And Pharaoh's wife said, \"Joy of the eye to me and thee! put him not to death: haply he will be useful to us, or we may adopt him as a son.\" But they knew not what they did"
  28,10,"And the heart of Moses' mother became a blank through fear: and almost had she discovered him, but that we girt up her heart with constancy, in order that she might be one of those who believe"
  28,11,"She said to his sister, \"Follow him.\" And she watched him from afar: and they perceived it not"
  28,12,"And we caused him to refuse the nurses, until his sister came and said, Shall I point out to you the family of a house that will rear him for you, and will be careful of him"
  28,13,"So we restored him to his mother, to be the joy of her eyes, and that she might not fret, and that she might know that the promise of God was true. But most men knew it not"